The follwoing is based on Bloomfield (1933), Aronoff (1976), & McCarthi (1989 & 1985).
Arabic language combines tense with aspect (how an action unfolds over time):

Perfective (completed actions) vs. Imperfective (ongoing/habitual actions)
Example in Arabic:
Perfective (Past): كَتَبَ (kataba – "he wrote")
Imperfective (Present/Future): يَكْتُبُ (yaktubu – "he writes/will write")
 													
